<TEXT>
The US navy <TIMEX2 val="PRESENT_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="2000-10-20T21:30:53.38" anchor_dir="AS_OF" comment="">now</TIMEX2> says the USS Cole was being refueled when an
explosion ripped through it in Yemen <TIMEX2 val="2000-W41" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">last week</TIMEX2>, killing 17. The
revised accounting of the incident was given in a navy statement
<TIMEX2 val="2000-10-20" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Friday</TIMEX2> raising new questions about how the small boat carrying the
explosives was able to get near the ship and set off the blast. 
